ENTRY       EC 2.3.2.20                 Enzyme
NAME        cyclo(L-leucyl-L-phenylalanyl) synthase;
            AlbC;
            cFL synthase
CLASS       Transferases;
            Acyltransferases;
            Aminoacyltransferases
SYSNAME     L-leucyl-tRNALeu:L-phenylalanyl-tRNAPhe leucyltransferase (cyclizing)
REACTION    L-leucyl-tRNALeu + L-phenylalanyl-tRNAPhe = tRNALeu + tRNAPhe + cyclo(L-leucyl-L-phenylalanyl) [RN:R10334]
ALL_REAC    R10334
SUBSTRATE   L-leucyl-tRNA(Leu) [CPD:C02047];
            L-phenylalanyl-tRNA(Phe) [CPD:C03511]
PRODUCT     tRNA(Leu) [CPD:C01645];
            tRNA(Phe) [CPD:C01648];
            cyclo(L-leucyl-L-phenylalanyl) [CPD:C20519]
COMMENT     The reaction proceeds following a ping-pong mechanism forming a covalent intermediate between an active site serine and the L-phenylalanine residue [2]. The protein, found in the bacterium Streptomyces noursei, also forms cyclo(L-phenylalanyl-L-phenylalanyl), cyclo(L-methionyl-L-phenylalanyl), cyclo(L-phenylalanyl-L-tyrosyl) and cyclo(L-methionyl-L-tyrosyl) [1].
